============================================================================
INTERPRETATION
============================================================================

  Each of the 500 time steps feeds its output into the next.
  This is the same sequential chain structure as the split-step
  Fourier method in DWDM fiber propagation.

  The drift column shows accumulated float error after the chain.
  VDR carries zero arithmetic error by construction.

  Symmetry: a symmetric implant MUST produce a symmetric profile
  after diffusion. VDR preserves this exactly. Float accumulates
  asymmetric rounding over 500 sequential steps.

  Dose conservation: diffusion must conserve total dopant count.
  Any drift in total dose is pure arithmetic error.

  For a process engineer: if the predicted junction depth differs
  between exact and float arithmetic, the float simulator's
  prediction of where the PN junction sits is contaminated by
  arithmetic noise. At sub-3nm nodes this feeds directly into
  threshold voltage variability predictions.

